sentence: Among the underlying components of the Russell 3000 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in Shake Shack Inc (Symbol: SHAK), where a total of 4,304 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 430,400 underlying shares.
That amounts to about 45.7% of SHAK's average daily trading volume over the past month of 941,675 shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $40 strike put option expiring March 17, 2017 , with 1,200 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 120,000 underlying shares of SHAK.

Plexus Corp. (Symbol: PLXS) options are showing a volume of 655 contracts thus far today.
That number of contracts represents approximately 65,500 underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 44.7% of PLXS's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 146,655 shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $50 strike put option expiring January 20, 2017 , with 207 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 20,700 underlying shares of PLXS.

Below is a chart showing PLXS's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $50 strike highlighted in orange:

And Home Depot Inc (Symbol: HD) saw options trading volume of 17,862 contracts, representing approximately 1.8 million underlying shares or approximately 43.9% of HD's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 4.1 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $130 strike put option expiring May 19, 2017 , with 1,020 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 102,000 underlying shares of HD.
